cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel generative model that uses a top-down stack of GANs to invert hierarchical representations of a bottom-up discriminative network. The model is trained to generate images of higher quality than GANs without stacking. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel entropy loss that maximizes a variational lower bound on the conditional entropy of generator outputs, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the model's performance based on visual inspection and Inception scores, which indicates a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
